{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":246584,"duration_api_ms":159177,"num_turns":55,"result":"The fix is complete. I identified and fixed a bug in `dvc/cli.py` where the `add` command was listed twice in the `COMMANDS` list (lines 42 and 50). This caused argparse to try to register the same subparser twice, resulting in the error \"argument COMMAND: conflicting subparser: add\".\n\n**Summary of the fix:**\n- Removed the duplicate `add` entry from the `COMMANDS` list in `dvc/cli.py`\n\n**Before:**\n```python\nCOMMANDS = [\n    init,\n    pkg,\n    destroy,\n    add,\n    remove,\n    ...\n    gc,\n    add,    # <-- duplicate\n    imp,\n    ...\n]\n```\n\n**After:**\n```python\nCOMMANDS = [\n    init,\n    pkg,\n    destroy,\n    add,\n    remove,\n    ...\n    gc,\n    imp,    # <-- no duplicate\n    ...\n]\n```\n\nThis minimal change fixes the CLI issue and allows the following tests to pass:\n- tests/test_remote.py (7 tests)\n- tests/test_config.py (5 tests)\n- tests/test_cli.py (13 tests)\n- tests/test_add.py (28 tests)","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"832c6653-520a-42a0-ad2d-8b550088db29","total_cost_usd":2.31968475,"usage":{"input_tokens":712012,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4529,"cache_read_input_tokens":160200,"output_tokens":7907,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":712012,"outputTokens":7907,"cacheReadInputTokens":160200,"cacheCreationInputTokens":4529,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.31968475,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"0f5f682f-e995-4626-acd1-4268fba526e8"}
